DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(88)90061-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407688900619
AB  - This paper develops a methodology to estimate transaction costs in arbitrage models. The methodology consists of the estimation of a generalized two-limit Tobit model with stochastic limits, and it provides the distribution of transaction costs and the probabilities of observing arbitrage in either direction. This methodology is applied to wholesale gasoline arbitrage among three cities in the Northeastern United States. Arbitrage costs are found to be relatively small.
ER  - 

