AU  - Shively, Thomas S.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 39
IS  - 3
SP  - 367
EP  - 386
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/11/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(88)90064-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407688900644
AB  - An exact small-sample point-optimal test is developed for testing the hypothesis that a regression coefficient is constant against the alternative that it is generated by a first-order autoregressive process. In addition, it is shown how Watson and Engle's (1985) asymptotic test can be modified so that its small-sample level can be computed and its small-sample power properties investigated. Simulation results show that the point-optimal test developed in this paperoutperforms the small-sample Watson–Engle test as well as other tests given in the literature. A point-optimal test is also constructed for a stochastic coefficient generated by an ARIMA (1,1,0) process.
