T1  - Prediction tests for structural stability
AU  - Lütkepohl, Helmut
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 39
IS  - 3
SP  - 267
EP  - 296
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/11/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(88)90059-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407688900590
AB  - Three groups of test statistics for testing structural stability are compared. The statistics are based on predictions from univariate time series models. The first group ignores the specification and estimation variability, the second group ignores only the specification uncertainty, while the statistics in the third group take into account both specification and estimation variability. Although corresponding statistics in the three groups have identical asymptotic distributions, their small sample distributions differ markedly. It is suggested to use the statistics in the third group in practice.
ER  - 
